PRIVACY POLICY

Effective Date: November 18, 2024

This Privacy Policy ("Policy") describes how TikTok Scheduler ("Company," "we," or "us") collects, uses, processes, and discloses your information, including personal information, in conjunction with your access to and use of the TikTok Scheduler service.

1. INFORMATION COLLECTION AND USE

1.1. Personal Information
In the course of providing our services, we collect and process the following categories of personal information:

(a) Authentication Information:
    - TikTok authentication tokens and credentials
    - Login session data
    - Account identifiers

(b) Service Usage Information:
    - Scheduling preferences and configurations
    - Post metadata and content information
    - Usage patterns and interaction data
    - Performance analytics and metrics

(c) Technical Information:
    - Device identifiers
    - IP addresses
    - Browser type and version
    - Operating system information
    - Network connectivity data

2. LEGAL BASIS FOR PROCESSING

2.1. We process your information based on the following legal grounds:

(a) Performance of Contract:
    - To provide and maintain the service
    - To execute scheduled posts
    - To manage your account

(b) Legitimate Interests:
    - To improve and optimize our services
    - To prevent fraud and ensure security
    - To analyze usage patterns

(c) Legal Obligations:
    - To comply with applicable laws
    - To respond to legal requests
    - To protect our legal rights

3. DATA SECURITY MEASURES

3.1. We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to ensure a level of security appropriate to the risk, including:

(a) Encryption protocols for data in transit and at rest
(b) Access control mechanisms and authentication procedures
(c) Regular security assessments and vulnerability testing
(d) Employee training on data protection and security
(e) Incident response procedures

4. DATA RETENTION AND DELETION

4.1. Retention Period:
We retain your personal information for as long as necessary to:
(a) Provide our services
(b) Comply with legal obligations
(c) Resolve disputes
(d) Enforce our agreements

4.2. Deletion:
Upon request or account termination, we will delete or anonymize your personal information, except where:
(a) We are legally required to retain it
(b) It is necessary for legitimate business purposes
(c) It is part of publicly available information

5. INTERNATIONAL DATA TRANSFERS

5.1. Data Transfer Mechanisms:
When we transfer personal information outside your jurisdiction, we ensure appropriate safeguards through:
(a) Standard contractual clauses
(b) Data processing agreements
(c) Adequacy decisions where applicable

6. YOUR RIGHTS AND CHOICES

6.1. Subject to applicable law, you may have the right to:
(a) Access your personal information
(b) Correct inaccurate data
(c) Request deletion of your information
(d) Object to or restrict processing
(e) Data portability
(f) Withdraw consent

7. THIRD-PARTY SHARING

7.1. We may share your information with:
(a) TikTok (for API operations)
(b) Service providers and subprocessors
(c) Legal authorities when required
(d) Business partners with your consent

8. COOKIES AND TRACKING

8.1. We utilize:
(a) Essential cookies for service functionality
(b) Analytics cookies for performance monitoring
(c) Preference cookies for user experience

9. CHILDREN'S PRIVACY

9.1. Our Service is not directed to individuals under the age of thirteen (13). We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.

10. CHANGES TO THIS POLICY

10.1. We reserve the right to modify this Privacy Policy at any time. We will notify users of material changes through:
(a) Email notifications
(b) Service notifications
(c) Website announcements

11. CONTACT INFORMATION

For any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us at:

Privacy Officer
Email: privacy@tiktokscheduler.com
Address: [Your Business Address]

12. SUPERVISORY AUTHORITY

You have the right to lodge a complaint with your local data protection authority if you believe our processing of your personal information does not comply with applicable data protection laws.
